  "prompt": "When entering the US will I be detained for a bench warrant?",
  "response": "If you have a bench warrant issued against you, there's a possibility that you could be detained when entering the United States. A bench warrant means that a judge has ordered your arrest because you failed to appear in court or comply with a court order. When entering the country, Customs and Border Protection (CBP) officers have access to law enforcement databases and might detect the warrant during their checks.\n\nIf you suspect you have an outstanding bench warrant, it\u2019s advisable to contact an attorney before traveling. They can provide guidance on how to resolve the warrant and potentially avoid detention.",
